column1: # Soil Total Carbon and Nitrogen by Depth - Deep Cores
# Original Data Source: https://lter.kbs.msu.edu/datatables/164
# The newest version of the data https://lter.kbs.msu.edu/datatables/164.csv
# Full EML Metadata: https://lter.kbs.msu.edu/datasets/47.eml
# These Data are copyrighted and use in a publication requires written permission
# as detailed in our Terms of use:  https://lter.kbs.msu.edu/data/terms-of-use/
# Use of the data constitutes acceptance of the terms.
#     VARIATE TABLE
# sample_date		date the sample was taken
# treatment		treatment the sample was collected from
# replicate		replicate that the sample was collected from
# station		station within the plot that was sampled
# core		there were 2 cores taken at each sample site. in 2001 core 1 was analyzed and core 2 was archived.
# section		slice of the deepcore
# section_length	centimeter	length of the section
# top_depth	centimeter	top depth of the core section in centimeters from the surface
# bottom_depth	centimeter	bottom depth of the core in centimeters from the surface
# core_volume_cm3	cubicCentimeter	the volume of the core section
# gravel_free_bulk_density	gramsPerCubicCentimeter	bulk density of the core section excluding gravel
# total_bulk_density	gramsPerCubicCentimeter	total bulk density of the core section including the gravel.
# n_percent	gramsPerHectogram	average percent N in the sample
# c_percent	gramsPerHectogram	average percent of C in the sample
# flag		outlier flag 'O'
# comment		comment about the sample
#        DATA TABLE CORRECTIONS AND COMMENTS
#2012-1-12. Sven Bohm. Discovered that T4 rep 6 had some sample_dates coded as 2006 rather than 2001. I've corrected the dates.

#2012-1-13. Sven Bohm. Included the core in the data. In 2001 we only analyzed core 1. I also discovered that the dataset included all the individual approved measurements. I changed it to report one average measurement for each treatment
#2022-12-14 Sven Bohm. Removed 2013 data at Phil's request.
#2019-3-28 Sven Bohm. treatment T1 replicate 1 station 1 and 2  and T6 rep 1 station 5 had samples that were re-run and the re-run samples were coded with the wrong sample dates
column2: This resulted in two sample dates for those stations in the output dataset. I updated the sample_dates on the rerun samples and excluded the original samples from the dataset.
